        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 4:53PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 453 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Rincon, moving northwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hatch, Rincon, Plactias, Rodey, and Angostura.

This includes Interstate 25 in New Mexico between mile markers 36 and
42.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
